SUMMARIZER="G">

Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher has announced she plans to step down after she leads 
her Conservative Party to a fourth successive election but was unlikely to try for a fifth.  
Critics say she has weakened her position and given the opposition a lead for success 
well before the actual race.  The next election must be held by the summer of 1992, but 
Mrs. Thatcher is expected to call it in 1991.

It is speculated that she would step down by 1994, the year she would celebrate her 69th 
birthday and her husband his 79th. Age may be a factor in her decision.</SUM>

<SUM
