SUMMARIZER="G">

A political sensation in Britain has been caused by Defense Minister Michael Heseltine's 
challenge to Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher for leadership of the Conservative Party. 
The first vote of Tory Members of Parliament is scheduled for today.  If Heseltine wins 
control of the party, Mrs. Thatcher would have to give up the Prime Minister's job she 
has held since 1979.

The editorial comment that has stirred Britain calls for: Mrs. Thatcher to stand down and 
preserve her achievements; the Party to rally to her support; rejecting her for not 
supporting European unity; support of Heseltine to defeat the opposition.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d076"
